Docs.summary: A structure encapsulating a four-dimensional vector (x,y,z,w), which is used to efficiently rotate an object about the (x,y,z) vector by the angle theta, where w = cos(theta/2).

remarks.format:
## Remarks The <xref:System.Numerics.Quaternion> structure is used to efficiently rotate an object about the (x,y,z) vector by the angle theta, where:
``` w = cos(theta/2) ```
